INSERT INTO `aggregator_item` VALUES ('68','4','NIH Common Fund Seeks Comments on mHealth Strategy','http://www.himss.org/ASP/ContentRedirector.asp?type=HIMSSNewsItem&ContentId=78037','','The National Institutes of Health (NIH) Common Fund, designed to fund transformative research that is of interest across the health community, is seeking comments on Innovative Mobile and Wireless Technologies (mHealth) to Improve Health Research and Health Outcomes.','1314368901','http://www.himss.org/ASP/ContentRedirector.asp?type=HIMSSNewsItem&ContentId=78037'),('69','4','California Model e-Health Community Awards announced','http://www.himss.org/ASP/ContentRedirector.asp?type=HIMSSNewsItem&ContentId=78038','','UC Davis Health System and the California Telehealth Network (CTN) have announced more than $5 million in awards to 15 community groups across California to advance health using telecommunications technologies and help provide examples of eHealth activity for other communities to follow.','1314368953','http://www.himss.org/ASP/ContentRedirector.asp?type=HIMSSNewsItem&ContentId=78038'),('70','4','Transforming Nursing Practice through Technology & Informatics','http://www.himss.org/ASP/ContentRedirector.asp?type=HIMSSNewsItem&ContentId=78050','','Nurses are key leaders in developing the infrastructure for effective and efficient health information technology that transforms the delivery of care. Recognizing this vital leadership role of nurses in providing quality patient care, the HIMSS Board of Directors approved a position statement describing how to transform nursing practice through technology and informatics. Leaders from the HIMSS Nursing Informatics Community, representing over 2,900 members who not only serve the nursing profession, but also, the broader healthcare industry and HIMSS membership at large, developed the position statement.','1314625831','http://www.himss.org/ASP/ContentRedirector.asp?type=HIMSSNewsItem&ContentId=78050'),('71','4','Where to Begin?','h