INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38174','38174','0','HHS Health IT Disparities Workgroup Seeks Public Comment on Draft Strategies','In a new Health IT Buzz Blog on the ONC website, Dr. David Hunt of ONC, and Dr. Garth Graham and David Dietz of the HHS Office of Minority Health are requesting public comment to assist the Health IT Disparities Workgroup as it develops a federal plan to reduce health IT disparities.','In a new Health IT Buzz Blog on the ONC website, Dr. David Hunt of ONC, and Dr. Garth Graham and David Dietz of the HHS Office of Minority Health are requesting public comment to assist the Health IT Disparities Workgroup as it develops a federal plan to reduce health IT disparities.','','1315927989','2'),('38175','38175','0','USDA and HHS sign MOU to expand Health IT Infrastructure in Rural Areas','On August 16, HHS and the US Department of Agriculture signed a Memorandum of Understanding launching two programs which will allow rural hospitals and clinicians to access capital loans enabling the purchase of health IT hardware and software.','On August 16, HHS and the US Department of Agriculture signed a Memorandum of Understanding launching two programs which will allow rural hospitals and clinicians to access capital loans enabling the purchase of health IT hardware and software.','','1315927989','2'),('38176','38176','0','NIH Common Fund Seeks Comments on mHealth Strategy','The National Institutes of Health (NIH) Common Fund, designed to fund transformative research that is of interest across the health community, is seeking comments on Innovative Mobile and Wireless Technologies (mHealth) to Improve Health Research and Health Outcomes.','The National Institutes of Health (NIH) Common Fund, designed to fund transformative research that is of interest across the health community, is seeking comments on Innovative Mobile and Wireless Technologies (mHealth) to Improve Health Research and Health Outcomes.','','1315927989','2'),('38177','38177','0','California Model e-Health Community Awards announced','UC Davis Health System and the California Telehealth Network (CTN) have announced more than $5 million in awards to 15 community groups across California to advance health using telecommunications technologies and help provide examples of eHealth activity for other communities to follow.','UC Davis Health System and the California Telehealth Network (CTN) have announced more than $5 million in awards to 15 community groups across California to advance health using telecommunications technologies and help provide examples of eHealth activity for other communities to follow.','','1315927989','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38178','38178','0','Transforming Nursing Practice through Technology & Informatics','Nurses are key leaders in developing the infrastructure for effective and efficient health information technology that transforms the delivery of care. Recognizing this vital leadership role of nurses in providing quality patient care, the HIMSS Board of Directors approved a position statement describing how to transform nursing practice through technology and informatics. Leaders from the HIMSS Nursing Informatics Community, representing over 2,900 members who not only serve the nursing profession, but also, the broader healthcare industry and HIMSS membership at large, developed the position statement.','Nurses are key leaders in developing the infrastructure for effective and efficient health information technology that transforms the delivery of care. Recognizing this vital leadership role of nurses in providing quality patient care, the HIMSS Board of Directors approved a position statement describing how to transform nursing practice through technology and informatics.','','1315927989','2'),('38179','38179','0','Where to Begin?','by Randy Pinnow<br />\nChair, Digital Office Task Force','by Randy Pinnow<br />\nChair, Digital Office Task Force','','1315927989','2'),('38180','38180','0','EU organization promotes green IT online','<p>The European Coordination Committee of the Radiological, Electromedical and Healthcare IT Industry (COCIR) has updated the &quot;Greening at COCIR&quot; section of its website to promote the importance of the environment in health IT.</p>\n<p>The purpose of Greening at COCIR is to update the European health IT industry on COCIR&rsquo;s activities, documentation and evaluation of potentially negative effects of current environmental legislative proposals.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/eu-organization-promotes-green-it-online\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>The European Coordination Committee of the Radiological, Electromedical and Healthcare IT Industry (COCIR) has updated the &quot;Greening at COCIR&quot; section of its website to promote the importance of the environment in health IT.</p>\n<p>The purpose of Greening at COCIR is to update the European health IT industry on COCIR&rsquo;s activities, documentation and evaluation of potentially negative effects of current environmental legislative proposals.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/eu-organization-promotes-green-it-online\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','','1315927989','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38181','38181','0','Beacon Communities snag more money for IT','<p>Eighty-five community health center programs, located in 15 of the 17 Beacon Communities nationwide, were awarded $8.5 million on Monday to aid with the adoption of health IT to support long-term improvements in quality of care, health outcomes and cost efficiencies.</p>\n<p>The awards, made available through  Health Resources and Services Administration (HRSA) under the Affordable Care Act, were announced by HRSA Administrator Mary Wakefield and National Coordinator for Health IT Farzad Mostashari, MD.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/beacon-communities-snag-more-money-it\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>Eighty-five community health center programs, located in 15 of the 17 Beacon Communities nationwide, were awarded $8.5 million on Monday to aid with the adoption of health IT to support long-term improvements in quality of care, health outcomes and cost efficiencies.</p>\n<p>The awards, made available through  Health Resources and Services Administration (HRSA) under the Affordable Care Act, were announced by HRSA Administrator Mary Wakefield and National Coordinator for Health IT Farzad Mostashari, MD.</p>','','1315927989','2'),('38182','38182','0','HIMSS Hosts Virtual Briefing on ICD-10 Conversion, Sessions Available On Demand','The HIMSS Virtual Briefing: Critical Success Factors of the ICD-10 Conversion held last week provided critical information to assist hospital professionals, ambulatory center leaders, practitioners, and their staff in transitioning to ICD-10. Session topics included planning for implementation and choosing a vendor partner.','The HIMSS Virtual Briefing: Critical Success Factors of the ICD-10 Conversion held last week provided critical information to assist hospital professionals, ambulatory center leaders, practitioners, and their staff in transitioning to ICD-10. Session topics included planning for implementation and choosing a vendor partner.','','1315927989','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38183','38183','0','HIMSS G7: Setting the Stage for \"Health-E-Biz\" with the HIMSS Interoperability Showcase&trade;','By John Casillas, Senior Vice President, HIMSS Business-Centered Systems','By John Casillas, Senior Vice President, HIMSS Business-Centered Systems','','1315927989','2'),('38184','38184','0','HIMSS G7 Meeting to Develop Use Cases for Interoperability Showcase at HIMSS12','September 14, Vanderbilt Center for Better Health','September 14, Vanderbilt Center for Better Health','','1315927989','2'),('38185','38185','0','HIMSS Announces New World Bank Task Force','The new HIMSS World Bank Task Force serves as the forum for partnership between the World Bank and HIMSS. Its purpose is to create opportunities to leverage global expertise in mobile health for the betterment of people’s health, particularly in developing countries.','The new HIMSS World Bank Task Force serves as the forum for partnership between the World Bank and HIMSS. Its purpose is to create opportunities to leverage global expertise in mobile health for the betterment of people’s health, particularly in developing countries.','','1315927989','2'),('38186','38186','0','HIMSS Medical Banking and Financial Systems Committee Sets Agenda and Goals','By Ted Perkins, MBA, CPHIMS','By Ted Perkins, MBA, CPHIMS','','1315927989','2'),('38187','38187','0','Meaningful Use, Patient-Centered Medical Home and ICD-10: The Health IT Investment \"Triple-Play\"','By Victor Freeman, MD, MPP','By Victor Freeman, MD, MPP','','1315927989','2'),('38188','38188','0','ICD-10 Transition Preparations: Start Now','By Dwan Thomas-Flowers, MBA, RHIA, CCS','By Dwan Thomas-Flowers, MBA, RHIA, CCS','','1315927989','2'),('38189','38189','0','HIMSS and 29 Organizational Participants Launch the ICD-10 PlayBook','As the deadline for HIPAA version 5010 looms around the corner on January 1, 2012, demand for information on ICD-10 implementation and risk mitigation continues to escalate.','As 