INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38190','38190','0','CMS to Host 5010 Testing Week Next Week','Jan. 1, 2012 is the deadline for the conversion to the ASC X12 Version 5010 transaction standards.','Jan. 1, 2012 is the deadline for the conversion to the ASC X12 Version 5010 transaction standards.','','1315927989','2'),('38191','38191','0','CMS to Host Medicare FFS Call on 5010, MAC Panel Q & A Session on August 31','The Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) will host its eighteenth national education call regarding Medicare Fee-for-Service (FFS) implementation of 5010 and D.0 transaction standards on Wednesday, August 31 from 1 – 2:30pm CT.','The Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) will host its eighteenth national education call regarding Medicare Fee-for-Service (FFS) implementation of 5010 and D.0 transaction standards on Wednesday, August 31 from 1 – 2:30pm CT.','','1315927989','2'),('38192','38192','0','Barry T. Ross, LFHIMSS, MBA-HAS, MSIE, DSHS','Barry T. Ross, LFHIMSS, MBA-HSA, MSIE, DSHS is a former president of HIMSS and is a recipient of the HIMSS’ 50 in 50 Award, which recognizes the memorable achievements to the field or body of knowledge of healthcare information technology and management systems. He received this award at the 2011 Annual HIMSS Conference &amp; Exhibition in Orlando on Feb. 22.','Barry T. Ross, LFHIMSS, MBA-HSA, MSIE, DSHS is a former president of HIMSS and is a recipient of the HIMSS’ 50 in 50 Award, which recognizes the memorable achievements to the field or body of knowledge of healthcare information technology and management systems. He received this award at the 2011 Annual HIMSS Conference &amp; Exhibition in Orlando on Feb. 22.','','1315927989','2'),('38193','38193','0','Single vocab standard for each EHR reporting domain seen as \'momentous\' (Government Health IT)','The Health IT Standards Committee has endorsed a single set of vocabulary standards and a single guide for putting them in place for each area of quality reporting measures.','The Health IT Standards Committee has endorsed a single set of vocabulary standards and a single guide for putting them in place for each area of quality reporting measures.','','1315927990','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38194','38194','0','2011 Congressional \"Asks\" for HIMSS 10th Annual Policy Summit Revealed','HIMSS has approved the recommendations of the Asks Task Force and the Public Policy Committee for the three priorities that participants in HIMSS’ 10th Annual Policy Summit will bring to Capitol Hill when they meet in Washington next month.','HIMSS has approved the recommendations of the Asks Task Force and the Public Policy Committee for the three priorities that participants in HIMSS’ 10th Annual Policy Summit will bring to Capitol Hill when they meet in Washington next month.','','1315927990','2'),('38195','38195','0','Congress Asks GAO to Study Wireless Medical Technology','Representatives Anna Eshoo (D-CA) and Edward Markey (D-MA) sent a letter this week to the Government Accountability Office (GAO), noting that while “Innovation in broadband and wireless enabled medical devices holds significant promise for enhancing health and reducing the costs of healthcare for all Americans','Representatives Anna Eshoo (D-CA) and Edward Markey (D-MA) sent a letter this week to the Government Accountability Office (GAO), noting that while “Innovation in broadband and wireless enabled medical devices holds significant promise for enhancing health and reducing the costs of healthcare for all Americans','','1315927990','2'),('38196','38196','0','Congressional Deficit “Super Committee”: Potential Implications for Health IT','HIMSS has prepared a fact sheet on the new Congressional “Super Committee,” including potential implications of committee deliberations for health IT.','HIMSS has prepared a fact sheet on the new Congressional “Super Committee,” including potential implications of committee deliberations for health IT.','','1315927990','2'),('38197','38197','0','Want to Make Your Voice Heard in Washington?','At a complimentary webinar last week, How to Have an Impact in Washington (now available on demand), HIMSS members heard from Washington insider Brad Fitch, President &amp; CEO of the Congressional Management Foundation.','At a complimentary webinar last week, How to Have an Impact in Washington (now available on demand), HIMSS members heard from Washington insider Brad Fitch, President &amp; CEO of the Congressional Management Foundation.','','1315927990','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38198','38198','0','Health IT Standards Committee Reviews Workgroup Recommendations','On Wednesday August 17th the Health IT Standards Committee (HITSC) convened virtually to discuss Standards and Interoperability activities and recommendations stemming from the various workgroups “Summer Camp” activities.','On Wednesday August 17th the Health IT Standards Committee (HITSC) convened virtually to discuss Standards and Interoperability activities and recommendations stemming from the various workgroups “Summer Camp” activities.','','1315927990','2'),('38199','38199','0','Federal Workgroup Seeks Anti-Counterfeiting Technology','On August 9, 2011 the United States Government Inter-Agency Anti-Counterfeiting Working Group published a Request for Public Comments Regarding Strategy to Eliminate Counterfeit Products from the United States Government Supply Chain. ','On August 9, 2011 the United States Government Inter-Agency Anti-Counterfeiting Working Group published a Request for Public Comments Regarding Strategy to Eliminate Counterfeit Products from the United States Government Supply Chain. ','','1315927990','2'),('38200','38200','0','President Announces Loan Program Expansion for Rural Hospitals to Invest in Health IT','President Barack Obama this week announced a package of investments to benefit rural communities. One of these investments is intended to support the purchase of health IT hardware and software.','President Barack Obama this week announced a package of investments to benefit rural communities. One of these investments is intended to support the purchase of health IT hardware and software.','','1315927990','2'),('38201','38201','0','NCSL Conference Includes Health IT Highlights','At its annual legislative summit last week, the National Conference of State Legislatures (NCSL) passed a resolution supporting National Health IT Week 2011.','At its annual legislative summit last week, the National Conference of State Legislatures (NCSL) passed a resolution supporting National Health IT Week 2011.','','1315927990','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38202','38202','0','Register Now for HIMSS12','The HIMSS12 conference is the destination for thousands of IT professionals, clinicians and healthcare executives from around the world who are seeking information and making decisions on how to move forward at this critical juncture. Meaningful use. ICD-10/HIPAA 5010.','The HIMSS12 conference is the destination for thousands of IT professionals, clinicians and healthcare executives from around the world who are seeking information and making decisions on how to move forward at this critical juncture. Meaningful use. ICD-10/HIPAA 5010.','','1315927990','2'),('38203','38203','0','Calls for 2011 HIMSS Annual Award Nominations and Scholarship Applications Now Open','The Calls for HIMSS’ 2011 Annual Award Nominations and Scholarship Applications are now open.','The Calls for HIMSS’ 2011 Annual Award Nominations and Scholarship Applications are now open.','','1315927990','2'),('38204','38204','0','HIMSS to Host Virtual Forum on ACOs','Accountability for the provision of care will have a profound impact on the delivery of healthcare as it shifts the government\'s reimbursement model from fee-for-service to one based on quality and efficiency.','Accountability for the provision of care will have a profound impact on the delivery of healthcare as it shifts the government\'s reimbursement model from fee-for-service to one based on quality and efficiency.','','1315927990','2'),('38205','38205','0','Organizations Invited to Participate in National Health IT Week','Initiated in 2006 by HIMSS, National Health IT Week has emerged as a landmark occasion for using health IT as part of the overall solution to improve America’s healthcare as a bipartisan, federally led, market driven initiative. NHIT Week 2011 will take place September 12-16.','Initiated in 2006 by HIMSS, National Health IT Week has emerged as a landmark occasion for using health IT as part of the overall solution to improve America’s healthcare as a bipartisan, federally led, market driven initiative. NHIT Week 2011 will take place September 12-16.','','1315927990','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38206','38206','0','News analysis: Remembering the health IT lessons that followed 9/11','<p>With the recent 10th anniversary of 9/11, there have been many personal and political remembrances of the events that scarred families and jarred the country that day. Health IT had its own significant events a decade ago, but they began about a week after 9/11 when letters with Anthrax in them were mailed.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/news-analysis-remembering-health-it-lessons-followed-911\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>With the recent 10th anniversary of 9/11, there have been many personal and political remembrances of the events that scarred families and jarred the country that day. Health IT had its own significant events a decade ago, but they began about a week after 9/11 when letters with Anthrax in them were mailed.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/news-analysis-remembering-health-it-lessons-followed-911\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','','1315927990','2'),('38207','38207','0','HHS, AT&T and AADE launch mHealth Initiative','<p>The Department of Health and Human Services&rsquo; (HHS), the American Association of Diabetes Educators (AADE) and AT&amp;T announced Monday an mhealth initiative to deliver diabetes self-management training.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\"></p>\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">The project will deliver diabetes self-management training (DSMT) project will be launched within an underserved minority community in Dallas, Texas.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/hhs-att-and-aade-launch-mhealth-initiative\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>The Department of Health and Human Services&rsquo; (HHS), the American Association of Diabetes Educators (AADE) and AT&amp;T announced Monday an mhealth initiative to deliver diabetes self-management training.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\"></p>\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">The project will deliver diabetes self-management training (DSMT) project will be launched within an underserved minority community in Dallas, Texas.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/hhs-att-and-aade-launch-mhealth-initiative\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','','1315927990','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38208','38208','0','GE launches new company to spur IT development','<p>GE has launched a new entity, Research Circle Technology, to accelerate and enhance the development of metabolic imaging and other technology.</p>\n<p>The mission of RCT, which was created under GE&rsquo;s Technology Ventures business, is to create an alliance between GE&rsquo;s scientists and the world&rsquo;s leading universities, officials say, providing access to GE&rsquo;s organic technology and healthcare expertise in an open innovation structure. INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38210','38210','0','Wellpoint to help IBM bring Watson technology to market','<p>IBM is teaming with WellPoint to develop the first commercial applications of its Watson technology, with an eye toward bringing evidence-based information to care providers.</p>\n<p>Watson is the computing system built by IBM that is intended to rival a  human&rsquo;s ability to answer question posed in natural language. Watson&rsquo;s  most public foray into proving its ability to handle the task was in its  appearance on the TV game-show Jeopardy! where it competed against and  twice beat two former champions.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/wellpoint-help-ibm-bring-watson-technology-market\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>IBM is teaming with WellPoint to develop the first commercial applications of its Watson technology, with an eye toward bringing evidence-based information to care providers.</p>\n<p>Watson is the computing system built by IBM that is intended to rival a  human&rsquo;s ability to answer question posed in natural language. Watson&rsquo;s  most public foray into proving its ability to handle the task was in its  appearance on the TV game-show Jeopardy! where it competed against and  twice beat two former champions.</p>','','1315927990','2'),('38211','38211','0','German hospital improves quality with radiology solution','<p>St. Marien-Hospital Borken will digitize its radiology operations with a new IT solution to improve efficiency and patient care, via a five-year agreement with medical technology company Sectra.</p>\n<p>Sectra&rsquo;s PACS will be implemented at the hospital to process and archive digital radiology images. The system will be integrated into the hospital&rsquo;s existing RIS and IT infrastructure.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/german-hospital-improves-quality-radiology-solution\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>St. Marien-Hospital Borken will digitize its radiology operations with a new IT solution to improve efficiency and patient care, via a five-year agreement with medical technology company Sectra.</p>\n<p>Sectra&rsquo;s PACS will be implemented at the hospital to process and archive digital radiology images. The system will be integrated into the hospital&rsquo;s existing RIS and IT infrastructure.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/german-hospital-improves-quality-radiology-solution\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38212','38212','0','Hospitals put out ‘Help Wanted’ sign for IT personnel','<p>While stubbornly high unemployment continues to drag on the rest of the economy, the healthcare industry can&rsquo;t seem to find enough qualified people to fill its information technology needs. Unlike other sectors where hiring remains muted, health systems are crying out for talent in IT, information management and coding, employment specialists say.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/hospitals-put-out-%E2%80%98help-wanted%E2%80%99-sign-it-personnel\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p>While stubbornly high unemployment continues to drag on the rest of the economy, the healthcare industry can&rsquo;t seem to find enough qualified people to fill its information technology needs. Unlike other sectors where hiring remains muted, health systems are crying out for talent in IT, information management and coding, employment specialists say.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/hospitals-put-out-%E2%80%98help-wanted%E2%80%99-sign-it-personnel\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','','1315927991','2'),('38213','38213','0','Obama\'s new rural jobs initiative includes health IT','<p></p>\n<p class=\"2subhead\"><strong>Seeks to increase access to workers and technology</strong></p>\n<p class=\"2subhead\">\n</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/obamas-new-rural-jobs-initiative-includes-health-it-0\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','<p></p>\n<p class=\"2subhead\"><strong>Seeks to increase access to workers and technology</strong></p>\n<p class=\"2subhead\">\n</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/obamas-new-rural-jobs-initiative-includes-health-it-0\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a></p>','','1315927991','2'),('38214','38214','0','News & Updates','<p class=\"debut\">Telehealth solutions provider, Independa has <a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/seniors-seeking-keep-their-independence-independa-offers-angela\">launched</a> &#8220;Angela&#8221;, a tool for older adults and seniors seeking independence. The interactive telecare platform provides various sorts of entertainment as well as communication facilitation with caregivers and family. It&#8217;s in an increasingly crowded market, with the GE/Intel JV Care Innovations as a major competitor.</p>\n<p class=\"link\">One mans&#8217; <a href=\"http://www.azcentral.com/business/articles/2011/07/03/20110703system-provides-icu-care-remotely.html\">personal story</a> exemplifies how a shortage of critical care specialists influences hospitals to turn to remote doctor&#8217;s for patient monitoring through use of eICU technology. Over three dozen hospitals in the U.S. are said to be providing care for critically ill patients, among the largest is The Banner Estrella Medical Center in Pheonix which implemented in 2006 what they call iCare, where this patient experiences care from a Doctor in Tel Aviv.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">At $512, Open PCR kits-copy machines for DNA- are <a href=\"http://openpcr.org/2011/07/dna-is-now-diy-openpcr-ships-worldwide/\">now</a> being shipped worldwide as in-home genomes that require only a set of screwdrivers to assemble.</p>\n<p class=\"study\">IBM study <a href=\"http://www.networkworld.com/news/2011/062911-ibm-healthcare-devices.html\">reportedly</a> surveyed over 1,300 wellness device users to better predict what the future holds for such tools. It is predicted that those to make the cut will be related to diet, elder care, true blood, mobility, and brain wave sensors.</p>\n<p class=\"partnership\">Google Health users will <a href=\"http://www.informationweek.com/news/healthcare/interoperability/231000712\">soon</a> be able to transfer their information to Microsoft Health Vault&#8217;s personal health record platform. Google Health is expected to close come January of 2012, with data available for download until January of 2013.</p>\n<p class=\"link\">Fast Company features CARE (Collaborative Assessment and Recommendation Engine), a proactive medical care software engine that emphasizes disease prediction and preventive treatment well before diseases manifest.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">We caught an early look at <a href=\"http://www.medify.com/\">Medfy</a>. It&#8217;s still in private beta, but has aggregated a huge volume of clinical abstracts which it machine reads, and presents to a user/patient in a new graphical manner. It&#8217;s at core a reinvention of the medical search process.</p>\n<p class=\"study\">Scripps Health and the West Wireless Health Institute (both of San Diego) <a href=\"http://www.signonsandiego.com/news/2011/jul/05/study-finds-portable-device-useful-quick-heart-exa/\">released a study</a> addressing the success of the GE VScan portable ultrasound device that is able to track ejection fractions from the heart as well as an EKG.</p>\n<p class=\"link\"><a href=\"http://www.healthdatamanagement.com/news/cms-core-hipaa-transactions-operating-rules-42733-1.html?ET=healthdatamanagement:e1867:187659a:&amp;st=email&amp;utm_source=editorial&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=HDM_Daily_070111\">Standards are rising</a> for HIPAA compliance when implementing electronic administrative and financial transactions, as the first two of many &#8220;operating rules&#8221; have been adopted by Medicare and Medicaid.</p>','<p class=\"debut\">Telehealth solutions provider, Independa has <a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/seniors-seeking-keep-their-independence-independa-offers-angela\">launched</a> &#8220;Angela&#8221;, a tool for older adults and seniors seeking independence. The interactive telecare platform provides various sorts of entertainment as well as communication facilitation with caregivers and family. It&#8217;s in an increasingly crowded market, with the GE/Intel JV Care Innovations as a major competitor.</p>','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38215','38215','0','News & Updates','<p class=\"event\">The FDA has <a href=\"http://www.latimes.com/health/os-health-apps-fda-guidelines-20110719,0,1863797.story\">issued</a> an extensive pamphlet covering guidelines for medical guidance apps.</p>\n<p class=\"partnership\">We recently <a href=\"http://www.health2news.com/2011/06/24/rip-google-health/\">mentioned</a> that Microsoft was planning to absorb help Google Health users move their data to Healthvault prior to its&#8217; closure. Microsoft&#8217;s tool that allows users to transfer PHRs has now been <a href=\"http://news.cnet.com/8301-10805_3-20080403-75/microsoft-offers-transfer-tool-to-google-health-users/\">launched</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"study\">We caught a demo of <a href=\"https://explorys.net/\">Explorys</a> out of the Cleveland Clinic which has arrangements with several large health systems. It takes, matches and integrates anonymous clinical data for research. It remains one of the most comprehensive clinical data sets (10 M lives) and has a nice business intelligence interface.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">Two artist-inventors are <a href=\"http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1342192419/pulse-sensor-an-open-source-heart-rate-sensor-that\">raising funds</a> to encourage the launch of their product- a pulse sensor-for compatibility with Arduino, an open-source electronic prototyping platform for interactive electronics.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Sanford Guide for prevention and treatment of infectious diseases has (finally) <a href=\"http://www.perituspr.com/2011/07/12/sanford-guide-begins-new-chapter-with-mobile-app-for-doctors/\">gone mobile</a>-now physicians can use the widely used reference guide via their smartphones and/or tablet.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">A <a href=\"http://www.auntminnie.com/index.aspx?sec=sup&amp;sub=ris&amp;pag=dis&amp;ItemID=95842\">new radiology data-mining tool</a>, REALM (RadLex Enhanced Auotomated Leximer Mining) was presented to The Society for Imaging Informatics last week and is being tested by our friends at Massachusetts General Hospital. The hope is to improve decision-support systems.</p>\n<p class=\"partnership\">The web-based physician network, Sermo, teamed with Johnson &amp; Johnson to develop their newly <a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/sermo-launches-mobile-app-immediate-access-physician-network\">launched</a> physician consultation mobile app, which is essentially an app version of their web network but it also includes iConsult an immediate crowdsourcing tool allowing other docs to comment on immediate clinical cases.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">For $202 M, the health care benefit provider Aetna, <a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/article/BT-CO-20110718-705943.html\">will buy</a> PayFlex Holdings, Inc. in order to improve the technical functionality of their products.</p>\n<p class=\"study\">Brazilian researchers have <a href=\"http://www.upi.com/Science_News/2011/07/18/Twitter-could-be-used-against-dengue-fever/UPI-44891311033341/\">developed</a> a software tool capable of using twitter to track Dengue Fever outbreaks. This is similar to the Google Correlates project work we <a href=\"http://www.health2news.com/2011/06/08/news-updates-17/\">mentioned</a> a few months ago.</p>\n<p class=\"link\">The NY Times published an <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/10/technology/bringing-therapists-to-patients-via-the-web.html\">article</a> revealing the attempts by telepsychiatry (which has been around for decades but is recently gaining widely usable recognition) to tap into the receipt of funding and acceptance by providers such as Medicare and Medicaid. The article covers examples of some companies and start-ups encouraging this change.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Dossia has <a href=\"http://informationweek.com/news/healthcare/EMR/231002035\">expanded</a> their personal EHR platform to one that encourages usability through action by patients, incorporating social networking and gaming.</p>','<p class=\"event\">The FDA has <a href=\"http://www.latimes.com/health/os-health-apps-fda-guidelines-20110719,0,1863797.story\">issued</a> an extensive pamphlet covering guidelines for medical guidance apps.</p>','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38216','38216','0','News & Updates','<p class=\"leadership\">The Departments of Defense and Veteran Affairs have <a href=\"http://articles.sfgate.com/2011-07-26/news/29815548_1_apps-mental-health-vets\">developed several mobile apps</a> for treatment and management of post-traumatic stress among veterans.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Northeastern University has <a href=\"http://www.technologyreview.com/read_article.aspx?id=38065&amp;a=f%5Burl%5D&amp;a=f\">developed</a> a new smartphone add on device that may eliminate the need for finger pricking among diabetics; nanosensors are injected beneath the skins&#8217; surface that picks up on glucose levels when using the light sensor smartphone attachment.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Kaiser Permanente has <a href=\"http://www.columbian.com/news/2011/jul/29/kaiser-permanente-creates-its-first-iphone-applica/\">launched</a> their first mobile phone application that allows members to utilize their location directory to find nearby facilities. Upcoming projects will include a mobile version of their online My Health Manager solution.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">The Center for Tech and Aging has <a href=\"http://www.cmio.net/index.php?option=com_articles&amp;view=article&amp;id=28878\">raised</a> $447K in mHealth grants to support the advancements of technologies for elderly with chronic conditions.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Numbered are the days of pagers; a <a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/news/2011/07/19/waltrham-co-launches-pager-for-the.html\">new app</a> allows doctors and paramedics to use iPhones as a replacement of the traditional pager. The paging system was designed for Apple, Inc. by communications company, OnSet Technology.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Medical reference, software developer Epocrates has <a href=\"http://www.eweek.com/c/a/Health-Care-IT/Epocrates-Launches-EHR-App-for-Apple-iPhone-Web-749788/\">finally launched</a> their new EHR which was initially announced 18 months ago. It is currently web based, and not yet mobile.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">Azumio, the developer of the Instant Heart Rate app has <a href=\"http://www.virtual-strategy.com/2011/07/27/azumio-raises-25-million-series-funding\">raised</a> $2.5 million in venture funding, which will enable the development of new apps including Stress Check and Stress Doctor. Funding donors include Founders Fund, Accel Partners, and Felicis Ventures.</p>','<p class=\"leadership\">The Departments of Defense and Veteran Affairs have <a href=\"http://articles.sfgate.com/2011-07-26/news/29815548_1_apps-mental-health-vets\">developed several mobile apps</a> for treatment and management of post-traumatic stress among veterans.</p>','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38217','38217','0','News & Updates','<p class=\"study\">Just in time for last weeks earthquake and hurricane on the East Coast, the American Red Cross distributed a <a href=\"http://www.redcross.org/www-files/Documents/pdf/SocialMediainDisasters.pdf\">survey</a> that revealed the increasing use of social media, online news, and mobile technology when in a state of disaster or emergency. Last Tuesday Health 2.0 helped launch the ASPR Lifeline Facebook <a href=\"http://www.health2challenge.org/2011/08/22/the-aspr-lifeline-facebook-application-challenge/\">Challenge</a>, and minutes later there was a 5.9 earthquake. Coincidence? Or did we plan it?</p>\n<p class=\"link\">A $500 million <a href=\"http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/08/24/google-reaches-500-million-settlement-with-government/\">settlement</a> between the Federal Government and Google has concluded the charges against Google for illegally allowing web advertisements of fraudulent Canadian pharmacies to be posted in the U.S.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">HHS <a href=\"http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/hhs-awards-137m-states-health-it-prevention\">awarded</a> $137 million in grants to invest in almost every state&#8217;s effort to utilize preventative health IT care tools and programs.</p>\n<p class=\"leadership\">Thanks to <a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/whitehouse/healthand-humanservicesregulatoryreformplanaugust2011\">regulations</a> that the Obama Administration has announced,  hospitals might find it easier to increase the use of telehealth. Hospitals should be able to save an estimated $13.6 million, and be able to undergo video consultations with patients therefore offering more access and care in rural areas. Of course, there are mixed <a href=\"http://www.usatoday.com/news/washington/story/2011-08-24/White-House-seeks-10-billion-savings-in-regulatory-rollback/50106728/1\">viewpoints</a> on the issue.</p>\n<p class=\"link\">Urology EHR vendor, Meridian EMR, <a href=\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/meridianemr-files-lawsuit-against-urochart-128172913.html\">filed</a> a law suit against a rival EHR vendor, Intuitive Medical Software, for allegedly accessing encrypted proprietary patient data from MeridianEMR&#8217;s system.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">Awarepoint Corporation, a real time location systems supplier for hospitals, <a href=\"http://www.sacbee.com/2011/08/24/3858106/awarepoint-corporation-secures.html\">received</a> $27 million of series F financing led by new investors Kleiner Perkins Caufield &amp; Byers, as well as Top Tier Capital Partners, Cardinal Partners, Venrock, and Jafco Ventures. Awarepoint plans to use the funding towards the expansion of its&#8217; &#8220;aware360platform&#8221;- a solution for mobilizing the healthcare environment.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Registry vendor <a href=\"http://www3.phytel.com/\">PhyTel</a> showed us a sneak peek at its&#8217; new interface that combines data visualization of a practice&#8217;s population with the ability to immediately contact the individuals concerned by e-mail, text, phone, and more.</p>\n<p class=\"study\">As EHRs open doors of opportunity for tracking and mapping disease trends and data, Scientific American <a href=\"http://blogs.scientificamerican.com/observations/2011/08/25/new-text-search-uncovers-disease-ties-and-safety-data-hiding-in-electronic-health-records/\">looks</a> at natural language processing as a way to extract data out of text. <a href=\"http://clinithink.com/\">Clinithink</a> is one new vendor we&#8217;ve seen that appears to be cracking the code.</p>','<p class=\"study\">Just in time for last weeks earthquake and hurricane on the East Coast, the American Red Cross distributed a <a href=\"http://www.redcross.org/www-files/Documents/pdf/SocialMediainDisasters.pdf\">survey</a> that revealed the increasing use of social media, online news, and mobile technology when in a state of disaster or emergency. Last Tuesday Health 2.0 helped launch the ASPR Lifeline Facebook <a href=\"http://www.health2challenge.org/2011/08/22/the-aspr-lifeline-facebook-application-challenge/\">Challenge</a>, and minutes later there was a 5.9 earthquake. Coincidence?','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38218','38218','0','News & Updates','<p class=\"study\">Social media is proving to play a valuable role in recruiting patients as participants in rare disease studies. Mayo Clinic conducted a <a href=\"http://www.minnpost.com/medcitynews/2011/08/31/31224/mayo_clinic_uses_social_media_to_recruit_rare_disease_study_participants\">study</a> of the poorly understood, fatal, and rare disease called Spontaneous Coronary Artery Dissection (SCAD). It was thanks to the online social group of survivors of SCAD that the Clinic was able to quickly enlist a large, diverse pool of contributors. Similarly, Patients Like Me was able to successfully recruit participants for real-time results in a <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/nbt/journal/v29/n5/full/nbt.1837.html\">study</a> for treatment evaluation of Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (back in 4/2010).</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">The ONC and the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation have designed and <a href=\"http://www.rwjf.org/newsroom/product.jsp?id=72782\">launched</a> a project called &#8220;<a href=\"http://www.careaboutyourcare.org/\">Care About Your Care</a>&#8221; in an effort to create a space for patients and consumers to better comprehend their care quality and the ways in which they might take participatory action.</p>\n<p class=\"partnership\">A partnership between American Well and Numera will leverage a new telehealth <a href=\"http://www.sacbee.com/2011/09/07/3890400/american-well-and-numera-join.html\">solution</a> that directly feeds health monitoring information into a live online interaction between patients and their physicians. American Well will contribute their online care suite technologies, while Numera will pitch in with their NET gateway; patients can input using their home monitoring devices. Such a solution will serve most beneficial for chronic condition patients as well as those who have more difficulty with mobility.</p>\n<p class=\"leadership\">Out with the paper, in with the iPads. Yale School of Medicine is <a href=\"http://www.boston.com/Boston/whitecoatnotes/2011/08/medical-student-essentials-stethoscope-ipad/inZJ4ayzxOm4cs4TBhGBhK/index.html\">equipping</a> students with iPads in an effort to save money and &#8220;go green&#8221;.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Medical documentation platform vendor MD-IT has <a href=\"http://www.pr.com/press-release/350911\">launched</a> its&#8217; android app, iConnect, which offers smart phone dictation and EMR access. The free product is offered through Google&#8217;s Android Market.</p>\n<p class=\"funding\">More incentives for rural health care access springs up; HHS has <a href=\"http://www.hhs.gov/news/press/2011pres/09/20110902a.html\">announced</a> their $11.9 million grant that will be dispersed to rural health networks to be used towards the implementation of HIT&#8217;s and HER&#8217;s. 40 organizations will receive $300,000 to spend on equipment, and related integration costs.</p>\n<p class=\"link\">It&#8217;s not just the (wo)manpower here at Health 2.0 who possess MBA&#8217;s in addition to their MD&#8230; A relevant article was published in the <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/06/business/doctors-discover-the-benefits-of-business-school.html\">New York Times</a> exposing this more common trend as Doc&#8217;s are encouraged to think more like entrepreneurs what with the tightening government regulations and insurance pressures.</p>\n<p class=\"debut\">Verizon Universal Identify Services-Healthcare that&#8217;s been around since November 2010 has now <a href=\"http://www.cioinsight.com/c/a/Latest-News/Verizon-Expands-Health-Care-ID-Service-to-Support-Mobile-Devices-EHRs-249338/\">expanded</a> to meet identity requirements for accessing EHR&#8217;s and HIE&#8217;s, and offers FDA approved digital signature for clinical documentation, e-pharma options for prescription distribution, and of course access through smartphones.</p>\n<p class=\"event\">The White House &#8220;Startup America&#8221; program has <a href=\"http://www.hhs.gov/open/initiatives/startupamerica/index.html\">expanded</a> its support of Health IT developers by featuring a group of &#8220;Innovation Exchanges for Health IT&#8221;. The Office of the Chief Technology Officer of the U.S. and the ONC are helping promote a series of meetings for Health organizations and Health IT developers who are nearing the proof-of-concepts stage in their development.</p>','<p class=\"study\">Social media is proving to play a valuable role in recruiting patients as participants in rare disease studies. Mayo Clinic conducted a <a href=\"http://www.minnpost.com/medcitynews/2011/08/31/31224/mayo_clinic_uses_social_media_to_recruit_rare_disease_study_participants\">study</a> of the poorly understood, fatal, and rare disease called Spontaneous Coronary Artery Dissection (SCAD). It was thanks to the online social group of survivors of SCAD that the Clinic was able to quickly enlist a large, diverse pool of contributors.','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38219','38219','0','Rep. Gingrey Uses Health IT as Example of Necessity for FCC Deregulation of Broadband','At a recent Institute for e-Health Policy Congressional seminar series event, Rep. Phil Gingrey (R-GA) criticized the Federal Communication Commission’s (FCC) new rules for “net neutrality” which prohibit fixed-line broadband providers from blocking access to websites and applications. According to Gingrey, the FCC’s “Open Internet” regulation will disincentivize the private sector from making critical investments in broadband, especially to rural parts of the country.','At a recent Institute for e-Health Policy Congressional seminar series event, Rep. Phil Gingrey (R-GA) criticized the Federal Communication Commission’s (FCC) new rules for “net neutrality” which prohibit fixed-line broadband providers from blocking access to websites and applications. According to Gingrey, the FCC’s “Open Internet” regulation will disincentivize the private sector from making critical investments in broadband, especially to rural parts of the country.','','1315927991','2'),('38220','38220','0','HIMSS Policy Priorities Show Progress','HIMSS’ 2011 Call for Action identifies ten health IT policy priorities for policymakers, including Members of Congress and the Administration. A new document posted online this week offers an update, identifying areas of progress towards these key goals. ','HIMSS’ 2011 Call for Action identifies ten health IT policy priorities for policymakers, including Members of Congress and the Administration. A new document posted online this week offers an update, identifying areas of progress towards these key goals. ','','1315927991','2'),('38221','38221','0','CRS Reports on Budget Control Act','The Congressional Research Service (CRS) has produced a report on the Budget Control Act of 2011, which raised the debt ceiling and established the Congressional “super committee” tasked with reducing the federal deficit by $1.5 trillion.','The Congressional Research Service (CRS) has produced a report on the Budget Control Act of 2011, which raised the debt ceiling and established the Congressional “super committee” tasked with reducing the federal deficit by $1.5 trillion.','','1315927991','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38222','38222','0','CMS Announces 2011 eRx Incentive Program Final Rule','This week the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services released a final rule for the Medicare Electronic Prescribing (eRx) Incentive Program for Calendar Year 2011. It contains two substantial provisions. First, the rule provides for an electronic prescribing incentive payment for eligible electronic prescribers. Second, the rule reduces the fee schedule payment for covered services for those professionals who are eligible but are not successful electronic prescribers. There are several exemptions for professionals who would incur significant hardship as a result of compliance.','This week the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services released a final rule for the Medicare Electronic Prescribing (eRx) Incentive Program for Calendar Year 2011. It contains two substantial provisions. First, the rule provides for an electronic prescribing incentive payment for eligible electronic prescribers. Second, the rule reduces the fee schedule payment for covered services for those professionals who are eligible but are not successful electronic prescribers. There are several exemptions for professionals who would incur significant hardship as a result of compliance.','','1315927991','2'),('38223','38223','0','VA Launches Open Source Custodian','The Veterans Administration (VA) and Department of Defense (DOD) are working to create a single electronic health record system for service members and veterans. As part of this goal, the VA is developing a new open source electronic health record (EHR) community that engages the public and private sector. The Open Source Electronic Health Record Agent (OSEHRA), which launched on August 30, 2011, will serve as the governing body of the initiative.','The Veterans Administration (VA) and Department of Defense (DOD) are working to create a single electronic health record system for service members and veterans. As part of this goal, the VA is developing a new open source electronic health record (EHR) community that engages the public and private sector. The Open Source Electronic Health Record Agent (OSEHRA), which launched on August 30, 2011, will serve as the governing body of the initiative.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38224','38224','0','FDA Public Meeting Will Discuss Mobile Medical Applications','The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has announced that it will hold a public meeting in September to discuss a draft guidance on FDA regulation of mobile medical device applications. The draft guidance, which was published on July 19, 2011, announced that FDA intends to regulate a large number of mobile medical device applications as Class I and Class II medical devices. Applications featuring the functionality of electronic health records and personal health records, as well as clinical decision support software, were not included in this guidance and will be addressed in future guidance, according to the FDA.','The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has announced that it will hold a public meeting in September to discuss a draft guidance on FDA regulation of mobile medical device applications. The draft guidance, which was published on July 19, 2011, announced that FDA intends to regulate a large number of mobile medical device applications as Class I and Class II medical devices.','','1315927992','2'),('38225','38225','0','NCSL Legislative Conference Resources Available','The National Conference of State Legislatures has posted resources from its recent Legislative Summit, including presentations from the session entitled “A Wealth of Knowledge: How the Health IT Revolution is Saving Lives and Dollars,” and policy positions on health IT.','The National Conference of State Legislatures has posted resources from its recent Legislative Summit, including presentations from the session entitled “A Wealth of Knowledge: How the Health IT Revolution is Saving Lives and Dollars,” and policy positions on health IT.','','1315927992','2'),('38226','38226','0','Meet Our Members: Todd Klein MBA, PMP, CPHIMS, CCNA','Todd Klein, MBA, PMP, CPHIMS, CCNA serves on the CPHIMS Technical Committee and is also a delivery service executive with Dearborn Advisors LLC.','Todd Klein, MBA, PMP, CPHIMS, CCNA serves on the CPHIMS Technical Committee and is also a delivery service executive with Dearborn Advisors LLC.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38227','38227','0','New England Journal of Medicine Study Shows Benefits of EHRs','The New England Journal of Medicine (NEJM) published a study, “Electronic Health Records and Quality of Diabetes Care”, which looks at care delivered to diabetic patients in physician practices that use electronic health records compared to physician practices that do not.','The New England Journal of Medicine (NEJM) published a study, “Electronic Health Records and Quality of Diabetes Care”, which looks at care delivered to diabetic patients in physician practices that use electronic health records compared to physician practices that do not.','','1315927992','2'),('38228','38228','0','Medicare & Medicaid EHR Incentive Programs: Registration and Attestation for Eligible Professionals (September 9, 2011)','Target Audience:\n\nEligible Professionals (EPs): Doctors of Medicine or Osteopathy, Doctors of Dental Surgery or Dental Medicine, Doctors of Podiatric Medicine, Doctors of Optometry, Chiropractors, Nurse Practitioners, Certified Nurse Midwives, Physician Assistants (PA) who practice at an FQHC/RHC led by a PA. (NOTE: Hospital-based EP’s may not participate- An EP is considered hospital-based if 90% or more of the EP\'s services are performed in a hospital inpatient or emergency room setting.)','Target Audience:\n\nEligible Professionals (EPs): Doctors of Medicine or Osteopathy, Doctors of Dental Surgery or Dental Medicine, Doctors of Podiatric Medicine, Doctors of Optometry, Chiropractors, Nurse Practitioners, Certified Nurse Midwives, Physician Assistants (PA) who practice at an FQHC/RHC led by a PA. (NOTE: Hospital-based EP’s may not participate- An EP is considered hospital-based if 90% or more of the EP\'s services are performed in a hospital inpatient or emergency room setting.)','','1315927992','2'),('38229','38229','0','Still Time to Register for the Policy Summit!','Please join us in Washington D.C. on September 14-15 for HIMSS 10th Annual Policy Summit? Registration is just $95, and includes breakfast, lunch, a reception, an Opening Speech by senior leaders of the U.S. Department of Commerce, a keynote speech from a physician Member of Congress, educational resources, networking opportunities, and personalized Congressional appointments pre-arranged by HIMSS staff. There are also opportunities to meet your Senators for coffee or breakfast when you’re in Washington, but you’ll need to RSVP. A special visit by a member of the Obama Administration is in the works too! Summit attendees are also invited to the National Health IT Week Networking and Awards Reception on September 14th.','Please join us in Washington D.C. on September 14-15 for HIMSS 10th Annual Policy Summit? Registration is just $95, and includes breakfast, lunch, a reception, an Opening Speech by senior leaders of the U.S. Department of Commerce, a keynote speech from a physician Member of Congress, educational resources, networking opportunities, and personalized Congressional appointments pre-arranged by HIMSS staff. There are also opportunities to meet your Senators for coffee or breakfast when you’re in Washington, but you’ll need to RSVP.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38230','38230','0','Super Committee Meets for First Time; Every Move Being Closely Watched','The so-called “Super Committee” met for its first official public hearing on September 8 to set the rules under which it will operate. The committee was created by the debt limit and deficit reduction legislation passed last July. Consisting of six Republicans and six Democrats, and divided evenly between the House and the Senate, this group is charged with finding $1.5 trillion in federal savings over the next ten years. The first hearing will be held during National Health IT Week, on September 13.','The so-called “Super Committee” met for its first official public hearing on September 8 to set the rules under which it will operate. The committee was created by the debt limit and deficit reduction legislation passed last July. Consisting of six Republicans and six Democrats, and divided evenly between the House and the Senate, this group is charged with finding $1.5 trillion in federal savings over the next ten years. The first hearing will be held during National Health IT Week, on September 13.','','1315927992','2'),('38231','38231','0','Continuing Resolution and FY12 Omnibus Appropriations on Horizon','We have learned that House leaders are expected to vote the week of September 19 on a continuing resolution to keep the government running into the new fiscal year, which begins on October 1. The Senate would almost certainly follow suit to avoid a federal government shutdown. Some are reporting that the continuing resolution would last through the fall, likely until November 18, the week before the joint deficit committee makes its recommendations on long-term spending cuts. This timing would give appropriators time to work on one catch-all FY12 omnibus appropriations bill for the entire government if individual spending bills cannot be completed.','We have learned that House leaders are expected to vote the week of September 19 on a continuing resolution to keep the government running into the new fiscal year, which begins on October 1. The Senate would almost certainly follow suit to avoid a federal government shutdown. Some are reporting that the continuing resolution would last through the fall, likely until November 18, the week before the joint deficit committee makes its recommendations on long-term spending cuts.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38232','38232','0','HIMSS Submits Comments on Interim Rule on Common Operating Rules for Eligibility','On Tuesday, September 6th, HIMSS submitted comments to the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services on the new Administrative Simplification interim final rule on Common Operating Rules for insurance eligibility. The operating rules are being adopted by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services as part of the requirements for Affordable Care Act of 2010 (ACA).','On Tuesday, September 6th, HIMSS submitted comments to the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services on the new Administrative Simplification interim final rule on Common Operating Rules for insurance eligibility. The operating rules are being adopted by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services as part of the requirements for Affordable Care Act of 2010 (ACA).','','1315927992','2'),('38233','38233','0','HHS Sends Breach Report to Congress','A new report to Congress reveals that 5.4 million individuals were affected by breaches of protected health information in the last year. The Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) reported 45 breaches that involved over 500 individuals and 5,521 breaches involving fewer than 500 in 2010. “The breach reports submitted to the Secretary in 2010 described five general causes of incidents, four of which were also reported in 2009: (1) theft; (2) loss of electronic media or paper records containing protected health information; (3) unauthorized access to, use, or disclosure of protected health information; (4) human error; and (5) improper disposal.”','A new report to Congress reveals that 5.4 million individuals were affected by breaches of protected health information in the last year. The Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) reported 45 breaches that involved over 500 individuals and 5,521 breaches involving fewer than 500 in 2010.','','1315927992','2'),('38234','38234','0','New HHS Funding Will Support Rural Health Networks\' Adoption of EHRs','Rural health networks across the nation will receive more than $11.9 million to support their adoption of health information technology (IT) and certified electronic health records (EHRs). The funding announced by HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius will also help these rural health networks’ participating eligible providers qualify for Medicare and Medicaid EHR incentive payments, administered by the Centers for Medicare &amp;Medicaid Services.','Rural health networks across the nation will receive more than $11.9 million to support their adoption of health information technology (IT) and certified electronic health records (EHRs). The funding announced by HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius will also help these rural health networks’ participating eligible providers qualify for Medicare and Medicaid EHR incentive payments, administered by the Centers for Medicare &amp;Medicaid Services.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38235','38235','0','ONC To Launch Consumer Education Campaign','In a new Health IT Buzz Blog, Lygeia Ricciardi, Senior Policy Advisor for Consumer e-Health in the Office of the National Coordinator for Health IT, discusses ONC’s plans for launching “a Consumer e-Health Program to equip and empower individuals to be partners in their own health and health care through health IT.” A public campaign, “Putting the I in Health ITSM [will use] stories to showcase how consumers and health care providers are partnering to use health IT to improve health and health care.”','In a new Health IT Buzz Blog, Lygeia Ricciardi, Senior Policy Advisor for Consumer e-Health in the Office of the National Coordinator for Health IT, discusses ONC’s plans for launching “a Consumer e-Health Program to equip and empower individuals to be partners in their own health and health care through health IT.” A public campaign, “Putting the I in Health ITSM [will use] stories to showcase how consumers and health care providers are partnering to use health IT to improve health and health care.”','','1315927992','2'),('38236','38236','0','ONC Launches Pilot to Establish Standards for EHR Data Queries','The Office of the National Coordinator for Health IT has launched an initiative to establish standards for requesting health data from widely distributed sources. The Query Health Initiative aims to develop standards and services that can distribute population health queries from certified EHR systems to network data partners. As part of the Query Health Initiative, ONC is soliciting members for several workgroups.','The Office of the National Coordinator for Health IT has launched an initiative to establish standards for requesting health data from widely distributed sources. The Query Health Initiative aims to develop standards and services that can distribute population health queries from certified EHR systems to network data partners. As part of the Query Health Initiative, ONC is soliciting members for several workgroups.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38237','38237','0','ONC Launches HealthIT.gov','The Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology (ONC) has announced the launch of its new website, HealthIT.gov. “This website is designed to become the leading national resource on health information technology (health IT) for both consumers and health care professionals…Whether you are a parent who is wondering how an electronic health record (EHR) will affect her family\'s privacy or a provider who is overwhelmed by the idea of transitioning to EHRs, HealthIT.gov has the resources to help answer your questions.”','The Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology (ONC) has announced the launch of its new website, HealthIT.gov. “This website is designed to become the leading national resource on health information technology (health IT) for both consumers and health care professionals…Whether you are a parent who is wondering how an electronic health record (EHR) will affect her family\'s privacy or a provider who is overwhelmed by the idea of transitioning to EHRs, HealthIT.gov has the resources to help answer your questions.”','','1315927992','2'),('38238','38238','0','New California Law Establishes Content for Data Breach Notification','California Governor Jerry Brown has signed into law Senate Bill 24, which, according to a summary by the bill’s author, State Senator Joe Simitian, “would strengthen the state’s security breach notification system by establishing core content for data breach notification. Information such as the type and time of the breach along with a toll-free phone number of major credit reporting agencies would be provided to consumers whose information was compromised. The bill would also require public agencies and people subject to the law to send an electronic copy of the breach notification to the Attorney General and the California Office of Privacy Protection if more than 500 Californians are impacted.” The law becomes effective on January 1, 2012.','California Governor Jerry Brown has signed into law Senate Bill 24, which, according to a summary by the bill’s author, State Senator Joe Simitian, “would strengthen the state’s security breach notification system by establishing core content for data breach notification. Information such as the type and time of the breach along with a toll-free phone number of major credit reporting agencies would be provided to consumers whose information was compromised.','','1315927992','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38239','38239','0','HIMSS Latino Community Collaborations Support Growing Health IT Needs of Hispanics','HIMSS Latino Community Collaborations Support Growing Health IT Needs of Hispanics','HIMSS Latino Community Collaborations Support Growing Health IT Needs of Hispanics','','1315927993','2'),('38240','38240','0','A Generous Approach to Patient Portal Design','By Kate Christensen, MD\nSeptember 2011, Clinical Informatics Insights','By Kate Christensen, MD\nSeptember 2011, Clinical Informatics Insights','','1315927993','2'),('38241','38241','0','A Clinician\'s Perspective on Transparency and Patient Empowerment','By David M. Liebovitz, MD\nSeptember 2011, Clinical Informatics Insights','By David M. Liebovitz, MD\nSeptember 2011, Clinical Informatics Insights','','1315927993','2'),('38242','38242','0','Going Beyond the Portal','By Sally Okun, RN, MMHS\nSeptember 2011, Clinical Informatics Insights','By Sally Okun, RN, MMHS\nSeptember 2011, Clinical Informatics Insights','','1315927993','2'),('38243','38243','0','President Signs NHIT Week Proclamation','US Secretary of Health and Human Services Kathleen Sebelius announced today the President signed a proclamation declaring September 11-16, 2011, as National Health IT Week.','US Secretary of Health and Human Services Kathleen Sebelius announced today the President signed a proclamation declaring September 11-16, 2011, as National Health IT Week.','','1315927993','2'),('38244','38244','0','Time Capsule: CCHIT&#8217;s First Certification List is Unsatisfying','I wrote weekly editorials for a boutique industry newsletter for several years, anxious for both audience and income. I learned a lot about coming up with ideas for the weekly grind, trying to be simultaneously opinionated and entertaining in a few hundred words, and not sleeping much because I was working all the time. They’re [...]','I wrote weekly editorials for a boutique industry newsletter for several years, anxious for both audience and income. I learned a lot about coming up with ideas for the weekly grind, trying to be simultaneously opinionated and entertaining in a few hundred words, and not sleeping much because I was working all the time. They’re [...]','','1315927993','2');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('38245','38245','0','HIStalk Interviews Todd Cozzens, CEO, Accountable Care Solutions &#8211; Optum','Todd Cozzens is CEO of the Accountable Care Solutions group of Optum.               \nGive me some brief background about yourself and your new job within Optum.         We were on our way to going public [...]','Todd Cozzens is CEO of the Accountable Care Solutions group of Optum.               \nGive me some brief background about yourself and your new job within Optum.         We were on our way to going public [...]','','1315927993','2'),('38246','38246','0','Monday Morning Update 9/12/11','From Jimmy Doogan: “Re: McKesson InSight conference September 20-23. Will HIStalk be covering? The tone will be interesting, as I would say the MPT part of the company hunkers down to milk their existing customers.” I wish I had the time to attend conferences, but it’s hard getting time off [...]','From Jimmy Doogan: “Re: McKesson InSight conference September 20-23. Will HIStalk be covering? The tone will be interesting, as I would say the MPT part of the company hunkers down to milk their existing customers.” I wish I had the time to attend conferences, but it’s hard getting time off [...]','','1315927993','2'),('38247','38247','0','Curbside Consult with Dr. Jayne 9/12/11','Mr. H’s recent Time Capsule on hospitals wanting software to do the dirty work of changing physician behavior is as true today as it was five years ago. All too often, we see the fallout of this strategy – poor adoption, user dissatisfaction, and worse.\nThe editorial mostly discusses CPOE, which was the hot ticket item [...]','Mr. H’s recent Time Capsule on hospitals wanting software to do the dirty work of changing physician behavior is as true today as it was five years ago. All too often, we see the fallout of this strategy – poor adoption, user dissatisfaction, and worse.\nThe editorial mostly discusses CPOE, which was the hot ticket item [...]','','1315927993','2